@startuml
title Apex Framework — Big Picture: Phases, Inputs, Outputs, and Literature Grounding

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle uml2
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam nodesep 45
skinparam ranksep 90
skinparam component {
  BorderColor #666666
  BackgroundColor #F5F5F5
  FontSize 13
}
skinparam note {
  BorderColor #999999
  BackgroundColor #FFFDF0
  FontSize 11
}
skinparam ArrowColor #333333
skinparam ArrowFontSize 11

rectangle "Strategic Alignment\n(Pre-Squad)" as P0
rectangle "Discovery &\nRequirements" as P1
rectangle "Design &\nPrototyping" as P2
rectangle "Implementation" as P3
rectangle "Testing" as P4
rectangle "Deployment" as P5
rectangle "Maintenance" as P6

note bottom of P0
  **In:** market signals, stakeholder ask,
  business constraints
  **Out:** approved Unit of Work + OKRs/KPIs
  **Lit:** single-threaded-leader ownership
  (Bryar & Carr, 2021) — closer precedent
  than a Spotify-style pre-Squad role
end note

note bottom of P1
  **In:** Unit of Work + OKRs
  **Out:** locked Gherkin acceptance
  criteria + stable spec IDs
  (functional-spec.md)
  **Lit:** Mob Elaboration (Raja SP,
  AI-DLC, 2025); epic-organized Gherkin
  outperforms per-scenario generation
  (Siddeeq et al., 2026)
end note

note bottom of P2
  **In:** locked Gherkin
  **Out:** locked Technical Spec + UX
  Brief + Runtime Contract
  (technical-spec.md, design-bundle.md,
  runtime-spec.md)
  **Lit:** "spec-driven development"
  (Thoughtworks, 2025) — direct precedent
  for anchoring the spec as the artifact
end note

note bottom of P3
  **In:** locked Technical Spec +
  Runtime Contract
  **Out:** developer packs; code passing
  Consistency Factor tests (Bolts done)
  **Lit:** Bolts / Mob Construction
  (Raja SP, AI-DLC, 2025); mandatory
  human validation answers documented
  AI-code security gaps (Zhao et al. 2025;
  Veracode, 2025)
end note

note bottom of P4
  **In:** implemented code +
  locked Gherkin
  **Out:** BDD-verified Story
  (qa_passed)
  **Lit:** LLM-generated BDD/Gherkin
  validated as a pattern, not just
  plausible (arXiv:2603.04729;
  arXiv:2508.20744)
end note

note bottom of P5
  **In:** qa_passed Story
  **Out:** deployed code +
  deployment-log.md
  **Lit:** DORA capabilities "strong
  version control" / "small batches"
  (DORA/Google Cloud, 2025)
end note

note bottom of P6
  **In:** deployed code + post-deployment
  feedback (bug / change request /
  monitoring signal)
  **Out:** classified signal routed to the
  owning phase, or a permanent Fix Log entry
  **Lit:** "AI is an amplifier" — governance
  determines which way it amplifies
  (DORA/Google Cloud, 2025); this phase is
  framework-original, not adapted from AI-DLC
  ----
  Explicit answer to being read as a
  linear/Waterfall model: Maintenance is
  not a dead end, and re-opening a phase
  is always a human decision, never automatic.
end note

P0 -right-> P1 : Unit of Work
P1 -right-> P2 : Gherkin
P2 -right-> P3 : Tech Spec
P3 -right-> P4 : Story built
P4 -right-> P5 : qa_passed
P5 -right-> P6 : deployed

' ---- governed loop-back: one consolidated arrow, not four crossing ones ----
P6 .up.> P1 : governed loop-back:\na classified signal re-opens the\nflagged phase (never patched blind)

@enduml
